3. Abstract

The Smart Farmers System is a MERN (MongoDB, Express.js, React.js, Node.js) full-stack application that connects farmers and buyers, allowing farmers to upload agricultural products and buyers to browse and purchase them. The project implements user roles (Admin, Farmer, Buyer), authentication using Clerk, and dynamic product aggregation with secure backend APIs.
The system was designed following the Software Development Life Cycle (SDLC) including planning, analysis, design, development, testing, deployment, and maintenance.
The project demonstrates clean architecture, modern UI, and real-world system modularity.

4. Introduction
Agriculture is one of the biggest sectors in Kenya. However, lack of market linkage between farmers and buyers leads to wastage, losses, and inefficiency.
The Smart Farmers System solves this by providing an online marketplace for farmers and buyers.

